@AndriySvyryd I just tried and this doesn't work as described. You can't compile this line `var items = nestedJson.ComplexCollection(j => j.Items);` becasue `j` is of type `Blog` not `NestedJson`

The workaround is to mark the whole complex property as modified like this `context.Entry(blog).ComplexProperty(b => b.NestedJson).IsModified = true` and that's probably what's most practical as it's super impractical to actually detect what exactly changed inside the complex property

